    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen placing signs using sign_place with 0 as the first parameter, if the first 2 signs are placed in different buffers, the sign id that is returned will be 1 for both of them. The subsequent sign ids are 2,3,4 ... regardless of where they are placed.\r\nThis does not happen when the first 2 signs are place in the same buffer.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean\r\nopen 2 different buffers\r\nrun `:lua vim.fn.sign_define('test', { text = 'A', texthl = \"\", linehl = \"\", numhl = \"\" })`\r\nrun `:lua print(vim.fn.sign_place(0, 'my', 'test', vim.api.nvim_get_current_buf(), {lnum = 1, priority = 11}))` in each buffer\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe printed output should be 1, 2. Instead you get 1, 1\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.8.3 0.9.0 0.9.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nubuntu 22 wsl\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\n-\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\n-\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
