            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I actually think we shouldn't try to replicate vim at all here and just rely on `extmark_set()` to return the proper id. So I got rid of `sign_group_get_next_signid()`. `extmark_set()` unconditionally increments but since it stores the ids per buffer you would still get [1, 1].\r\nI think that is fine since legacy signs and now extmark signs are unique to a buffer anyways.",
